Manchester United star player, Cristiano Ronaldo, on Monday appreciated his fans over his record breaking feat of acquiring 400 million Instagram followers. The football champion, who’s currently at 404 million, became the most followed person on Instagram two weeks ago, when he exceeded 400 million followers. Appreciating his fans on Monday, Ronaldo noted that it was a fantastic moment for him. “Without you, this would not be possible. So from the bottom of my heart, I have to say thank you,” the football star said in a video shared on his Instagram page. He also revealed his intentions to gain more followers in hundreds and millions. Watch video below:  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com